    <div id="popupdiv0" class="calevent" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;"><div class="roundeddivtitle" style="color:#f7f7f7;font-weight:bold;font-size:medium;padding-top:3px;padding-bottom:3px;"><div style="float:right;"><a href="#" onclick="popupEvent(-1);return false;" style="cursor:pointer;color:#d6a221;font-weight:bold;font-size:medium;margin-right:15px;">Close [X]</a></div><span style="margin-left:15px;">Corks & Hops in Crestline</span></div><div style="padding:10px;"><br /><i>Saturday, September 2, 2017 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3:00 PM - 8:00 PM</i><hr /><div id="popupscroll0" style="overflow-y:auto;width:100%;"><div style="min-height:260px;"><div style='font-family:  Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:Small;'>Enjoy wine and craft beer as well as fare from local restaurants and live music in beautiful downtown Crestline during this monthly event.&nbsp;</div><br /><span style="color:#738AAD;font-size:Small;"></div><hr /> Published May 3, 2017  -  By </span><a href="http://www.sbcounty.gov/BOSD2/default.aspx" style="color:#245AA8;font-size:Small;">Board of Supervisors District 2</a></div></div></div>
<div id="popupdiv1" class="calevent" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;"><div class="roundeddivtitle" style="color:#f7f7f7;font-weight:bold;font-size:medium;padding-top:3px;padding-bottom:3px;"><div style="float:right;"><a href="#" onclick="popupEvent(-1);return false;" style="cursor:pointer;color:#d6a221;font-weight:bold;font-size:medium;margin-right:15px;">Close [X]</a></div><span style="margin-left:15px;">Mauka Makai Luau at Lake Gregory</span></div><div style="padding:10px;"><br /><i>Saturday, September 2, 2017 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6:30 PM - 10:00 PM</i><hr /><div id="popupscroll1" style="overflow-y:auto;width:100%;"><div style="min-height:260px;"><div style='font-family:  Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:Small;'><div>Enjoy a captivating luau on the shores of Lake Gregory with hula dancing, spellbinding drummers, the show-stopping fire-knife performer, and a magnificent Hawaiian feast. Bring your appetite. Celebrate the spirit of aloha with authentic traditional luau foods that blend Hawaiian, Polynesian and Asian-influenced flavors.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>We will begin with the rhythmic drums of Tahiti and the haunting echo of the conch shell as Na Pualei Ohana, "the cherished family", takes you on an unforgettable visual journey through the islands of Polynesia.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Dancers dazzle you with colorful costuming, songs and dances from the islands of Hawaii, Tahiti, and New Zealand, culminating in the highlight of our Samoan chief doing his warrior’s fire knife dance.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>When Hula dancers make their way into the audience to find some volunteers, be prepared to join in the fun!
